<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="299" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="4.[136,1452,433,737]" pageId="4" pageNumber="299">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[136,201,433,459]" pageId="4" pageNumber="299">Note:</emphasis>
The current name 
<taxonomicName authority="(Franch.) E. Pritz." authorityName="E. Pritz." baseAuthorityName="Franch." box="[412,804,433,460]" class="Pinopsida" family="Pinaceae" genus="Picea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pinales" pageId="4" pageNumber="299" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="brachytyla">
<emphasis box="[412,602,433,459]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="299">Picea brachytyla</emphasis>
(Franch.) E.Pritz.
</taxonomicName>
is based on 
<taxonomicName authority="Franch. In" authorityName="Franch. In" box="[941,1252,433,459]" class="Pinopsida" family="Pinaceae" genus="Abies" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pinales" pageId="4" pageNumber="299" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="brachytyla">
<emphasis box="[941,1130,433,459]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="299">Abies brachytyla</emphasis>
Franch. In
</taxonomicName>
the protologue of 
<taxonomicName authority=", Franchet (1899)" authorityName=", Franchet" authorityYear="1899" box="[136,521,467,494]" class="Pinopsida" family="Pinaceae" genus="Abies" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pinales" pageId="4" pageNumber="299" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="brachytyla">
<emphasis box="[136,333,467,493]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="299">Abies brachytyla,</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Franchet, A. R." box="[341,521,467,494]" pageId="4" pageNumber="299" pagination="253 - 266" refId="ref2081" refString="Franchet, A. R. (1899) Plantarum sinensium ecloge tertia. Journal de Botanique 13 (8): 253 - 266." type="journal article" year="1899">Franchet (1899)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
cited two gatherings (
<emphasis box="[776,927,467,493]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="299">J.M. Delavay</emphasis>
4129 and 
<emphasis box="[1047,1181,468,494]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="299">P.G. Farges</emphasis>
806) and they are to be considered as 
<typeStatus box="[298,400,503,529]" pageId="4" pageNumber="299">syntypes</typeStatus>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Farjon, A." box="[411,561,502,528]" pageId="4" pageNumber="299" refId="ref1924" refString="Farjon, A. (2010) A handbook of the world's conifers. Brill, Leiden &amp; Boston, 1112 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.1163 / 9789047430629" type="book" year="2010">Farjon (2010</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Farjon, A." box="[574,632,502,528]" pageId="4" pageNumber="299" refId="ref1957" refString="Farjon, A. (2017) A handbook of the world's conifers. 2 nd ed. Brill, Leiden &amp; Boston, 1154 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.1163 / 9789004324510" type="book" year="2017">2017</bibRefCitation>
) mentioned the 
<typeStatus box="[818,916,503,529]" pageId="4" pageNumber="299">syntypes</typeStatus>
at P for the name of this species and indicated that a type had not been designated, however already Rehder &amp; Wilson (1914: 33) had accomplished a first-step lectotypification by citing 
<emphasis box="[432,560,571,597]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="299">Farges 806</emphasis>
as “type” but without indicating a herbarium of deposit. Because this gathering is represented in several herbaria, to fix the application of this name, we select a specimen with cone from one of the gatherings at P (P00731326) as a second-step 
<typeStatus box="[650,753,641,667]" pageId="4" pageNumber="299">lectotype</typeStatus>
(
<figureCitation box="[768,837,641,667]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="2.[136,229,2028,2050]" captionTargetBox="[198,1385,205,2004]" captionTargetId="figure-23@2.[188,1400,190,2004]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 2. Picea brachytyla (Franch.) E. Pritz. (lectotype). © MNHN collection-Paris." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6650937" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6650937/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="299">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
). Although the same specimen was annotated “Type of 
<taxonomicName authority="Franch." authorityName=", Franchet" authorityYear="1899" box="[136,420,675,701]" class="Pinopsida" family="Pinaceae" genus="Abies" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pinales" pageId="4" pageNumber="299" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="brachytyla">
<emphasis box="[136,325,675,701]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="299">Abies brachytyla</emphasis>
Franch.
</taxonomicName>
” by Fu and Li in 1995 and bears a “[LECTO] TYPE” herbarium sticker, this seems never to have been effectively published until now.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
